{"questionId":"9075752","questionHtml":"<p>A stone of mass <em>m</em> is projected vertically upwards with speed <em>u</em> from the top of a cliff. The speed of the stone when it is just about to hit the ground is <em>v</em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7caa5410c4c2c7b688aab175ac00262bc499c31e.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the magnitude of the change in momentum of the stone?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>u</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>u</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9075752","referenceCode":"23M.1.HL.TZ1.4","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A stone of mass m is projected vertically upwards with speed u from the top of a cliff. The speed of the stone when it is just about to hit the ground is v. What is the magnitude o","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"4","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.3 – Work, energy, and power","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}